for some formula_25. For any bounded variable , formula_26 for formula_27 for some sufficiently large . Then formula_28 for all formula_29 so taking formula_30 yields

:formula_31

for formula_29. So every bounded variable is sub-Gaussian.

For a random variable , the following norm is finite if and only if is sub-Gaussian:

